### **Export Optimization**
Prepare documents for professional sharing:

```markdown
# Document Export Guidelines

## For PDF Export
- Use clear headings hierarchy (H1, H2, H3)
- Include table of contents with internal links
- Optimize images for print (avoid very wide images)
- Use page breaks with `---` where appropriate

## For Word Export  
- Keep formatting simple for best conversion
- Use standard markdown syntax
- Avoid complex HTML embedded in markdown
- Test exports before sharing with stakeholders

## Professional Presentation
- Include cover page with title and date
- Add footer with document path for reference
- Use consistent terminology throughout
- Include version information when relevant
```

